                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d230">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Powell</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Loomis states that no definite information has reached this Department as to
                    the prevailing conditions in Santo Domingo, and asks Mr. Powell if the stability
                    of either the provisional or Jiminez government is sufficient to justify formal
                    recognition.)</p>
            </div>
